          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">I=100 × left [n+(N-n) {log {left ({t} rsub {r(unknown)} rsup {'} right )} -log⁡( {t} rsub {r(n)} rsup {'} )} over {log {left ({t} rsub {r( {N} ^ {'} )} rsup {'} right )} -log⁡( {t} rsub {r(n)} rsup {'} )} right ]</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation>

<para id="import-auto-idm504536064">Suppose researchers ran an initial GC and obtained the following retention times for methane, hexane, and decane: 0.5, 12.3, and 18.5 minutes respectively. An unknown alkane has a retention time of 14.7; what is the retention index for the unknown?</para>
</problem>

<solution id="eip-85">
  <para id="eip-617">This question requires previous knowledge regarding nomenclature of organic compounds and understanding that retention time for methane will be used to calculate the adjusted retention times for the other molecules. Hexane contains 6 carbons while decane contains 10, meaning the variable N will refer to decane and the variable n will refer to hexane. The adjusted retention time for hexane, decane, and the unknown compound are 11.8, 18.0, and 14.2, respectively. To solve for I, the values are plugged into:</para>
<equation id="eip-418"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mi>I</m:mi>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>100</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mi>×</m:mi>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">[</m:mo>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mn>10</m:mn>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                          <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mfrac>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mi>log</m:mi>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">(</m:mo>
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mn>14.2</m:mn>
                          </m:mrow>
                          <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">)</m:mo>
                        </m:mrow>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                        <m:mi>log</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mi>⁡</m:mi>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mn>11.8</m:mn>
                        </m:mrow>
                        <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mrow>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mi>log</m:mi>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">(</m:mo>
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mn>18.0</m:mn>
                          </m:mrow>
                          <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">)</m:mo>
                        </m:mrow>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                        <m:mi>log</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mi>⁡</m:mi>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mn>11.8</m:mn>
                        </m:mrow>
                        <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mfrac>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">]</m:mo>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">I=100 × left [6 +( 10 - 6 ) {log {left (14.2 right )} -log⁡( 11.8 )} over {log {left (18.0 right )} -log⁡( 11.8 )} right ]</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation><para id="import-auto-idm488294624">After solving the equation, the retention index for the unknown compound = 775. </para>
</solution>
</exercise>
       



        
        <exercise id="eip-548"><problem id="eip-633">
  <para id="eip-622">As mentioned in the paper, calculating the concentration of metal in water waste has proven to be a key issue for oil companies; therefore, multiple methods have been developed to assess the efficiency of this calculation. The metal-complexing ligand (EDTA, <link target-id="import-auto-idm753435408XCZ1ZC"/>) is one of the more popular choices when trying to determine the concentration of metal in a sample. A very helpful piece of information for researchers is the complexometric titration curve, which plots the p(Metal) vs. the volume of EDTA added. Given that β<sub>4 </sub>equals 8 x 10<sup>-6</sup>, calculate the pFe of a mixture when 40 mL of 0.001 M EDTA has been added to a 60 mL solution of 0.001 M Fe<sup>2+</sup>. This pFe will correspond to one point along the titration curve for iron and EDTA.</para>
  <figure id="import-auto-idm753435408XCZ1ZC"><media id="import-auto-idm574037904XCZ1ZC" alt="">
            <image mime-type="image/jpg" src="../../media/EDTA.jpg" width="200" print-width="2in"/>
          </media>
        <caption>Structure of ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid (EDTA). </caption></figure></problem>

<solution id="eip-726">
  <para id="eip-891">To solve this question, two main equations need to be known. The first relates the total concentration of the species that has not complexed with EDTA to the volume of the solutions; the second relates the effective stability constant to the concentration of the metal ion in the sample: </para>

<equation id="eip-481"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:msub>
              <m:mi>C</m:mi>
              <m:mi mathvariant="italic">Fe</m:mi>
            </m:msub>
            <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
            <m:mfrac>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                      <m:mi>R</m:mi>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>M</m:mi>
                        <m:mi>R</m:mi>
                      </m:msub>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                      <m:msub>
                        <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                        <m:mi>T</m:mi>
                      </m:msub>
                    </m:mrow>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>M</m:mi>
                      <m:mi>T</m:mi>
                    </m:msub>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                      <m:mi>R</m:mi>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                      <m:mi>T</m:mi>
                    </m:msub>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mfrac>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">{C} rsub {Fe}  =  {( {V} rsub {R} {M} rsub {R}  -  {V} rsub {T} {M} rsub {T} )} over {( {V} rsub {R}  +  {V} rsub {T} ) }</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation><equation id="eip-143"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>C</m:mi>
                <m:mi mathvariant="italic">Fe</m:mi>
              </m:msub>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mfrac>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">[</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">(</m:mo>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mn>60</m:mn>
                            <m:mi>×</m:mi>
                            <m:mn>0.001</m:mn>
                          </m:mrow>
                        </m:mrow>
                        <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">)</m:mo>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">(</m:mo>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mn>40</m:mn>
                            <m:mi>×</m:mi>
                            <m:mn>0.001</m:mn>
                          </m:mrow>
                        </m:mrow>
                        <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">)</m:mo>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">]</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mn>60</m:mn>
                      <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
                      <m:mn>40</m:mn>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mfrac>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mi>x</m:mi>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mn>10</m:mn>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                <m:mn>4</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:msup>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">{C} rsub {Fe}  = {[ left (60 × 0.001 right ) - left (40 × 0.001 right ) ]} over {(60+40)}  = 2 x  {10} ^ {-4}     M</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation><equation id="eip-545"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>C</m:mi>
                <m:mi mathvariant="italic">Fe</m:mi>
              </m:msub>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mi>x</m:mi>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mn>10</m:mn>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                <m:mn>4</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:msup>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">{C} rsub {Fe}  = 2 x  {10} ^ {-4}   M</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation><para id="eip-423">Thus, </para><equation id="eip-737"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:msub>
              <m:mi>β</m:mi>
              <m:mn>4</m:mn>
            </m:msub>
            <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
            <m:mfrac>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">[</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi mathvariant="italic">Fe</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">]</m:mo>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>C</m:mi>
                <m:mi mathvariant="italic">Fe</m:mi>
              </m:msub>
            </m:mfrac>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">{β} rsub {4}  =  {[Fe ]} over {{C} rsub {Fe}}  </m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation><para id="eip-940">Rearrange to: </para><equation id="eip-552"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:msub>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">[</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="italic">Fe</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">]</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                <m:mi>β</m:mi>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mn>4</m:mn>
            </m:msub>
            <m:mi>×</m:mi>
            <m:msub>
              <m:mi>C</m:mi>
              <m:mi mathvariant="italic">Fe</m:mi>
            </m:msub>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">{[ Fe ]  =  β} rsub {4}  ×  {C} rsub {Fe}  </m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation><equation id="eip-301"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">[</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi mathvariant="italic">Fe</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">]</m:mo>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">(</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>8</m:mn>
                    <m:mi>×</m:mi>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mn>10</m:mn>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                        <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:msup>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">)</m:mo>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mi>×</m:mi>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">(</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    <m:mi>×</m:mi>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mn>10</m:mn>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                        <m:mn>4</m:mn>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:msup>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">)</m:mo>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>1.6</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mi>×</m:mi>
            <m:msup>
              <m:mn>10</m:mn>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                <m:mn>9</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:msup>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">  left [Fe right ] = left (8  ×   {10} ^ {-6} right )   ×  left (2  ×   {10} ^ {-4} right ) = 1.6  ×   {10} ^ {-9}  M</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation><para id="eip-352">β<sub>4</sub> × C<sub>Fe</sub> = [Fe<sup>2+</sup>] = 8 x 10<sup>-6</sup> × 2 x 10<sup>-4</sup> = 1.6 x 10<sup>-9</sup> M. </para><para id="eip-815">Finally, convert the molar concentration into the pFe, where the -log(Fe<sup>2+</sup>) will be calculated: </para><equation id="eip-899"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
              <m:mi>log</m:mi>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>1.6</m:mn>
                    <m:mi>×</m:mi>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mn>10</m:mn>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                        <m:mn>9</m:mn>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:msup>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>8.80</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">-log(1.6  ×     {10} ^ {-9} ) = 8.80</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation>




</solution>


</exercise>




<exercise id="eip-855"><problem id="eip-177">
  <para id="eip-941">A reaction that occurs in most combustion tanks includes the combustion of octane, a hydrocarbon representative of most gasoline products (<link target-id="eip-160"/>). Given that the density of gasoline is around 0.75 kg/L, what is the mass of oxygen (kg) that is needed to react with 30 L of gasoline?</para><equation id="eip-160"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            <m:msub>
              <m:mi>C</m:mi>
              <m:mn>8</m:mn>
            </m:msub>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>H</m:mi>
                <m:mn>18</m:mn>
              </m:msub>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
              <m:mn>25</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:msub>
              <m:mi>O</m:mi>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msub>
            <m:mi>→</m:mi>
            <m:mn>16</m:mn>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi mathvariant="italic">CO</m:mi>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn>
              </m:msub>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
              <m:mn>18</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:msub>
              <m:mi>H</m:mi>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msub>
            <m:mi>O</m:mi>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">2  {C} rsub {8} {H} rsub {18}  + 25  {O} rsub {2} → 16  {CO} rsub {2}  + 18  {H} rsub {2} O</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation>
</problem>

<solution id="eip-972">
  <para id="eip-333">The molecular weight of C<sub>8</sub>H<sub>18</sub> = 114.22 g/mol. We proceed to convert liters of gas to moles of gas, and then use stoichiometric relations to obtain the O<sub>2</sub> required to react fully with all the gas.</para>
<equation id="eip-795"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>30</m:mn>
            <m:mi>L</m:mi>
            <m:msub>
              <m:mi>C</m:mi>
              <m:mn>8</m:mn>
            </m:msub>
            <m:msub>
              <m:mi>H</m:mi>
              <m:mn>18</m:mn>
            </m:msub>
            <m:mi>×</m:mi>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">(</m:mo>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mfrac>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>0.75</m:mn>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="italic">kg</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    <m:mi>L</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mfrac>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">)</m:mo>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mi>×</m:mi>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">(</m:mo>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mfrac>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>1000</m:mn>
                    <m:mi>g</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="italic">kg</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mfrac>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">)</m:mo>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mi>×</m:mi>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">(</m:mo>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mfrac>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="italic">mol</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>114.22</m:mn>
                    <m:mi>g</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mfrac>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">)</m:mo>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mi>×</m:mi>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">(</m:mo>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mfrac>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>25</m:mn>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="italic">mol</m:mi>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>O</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="italic">mol</m:mi>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>C</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>8</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                    <m:msub>
                      <m:mi>H</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>18</m:mn>
                    </m:msub>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mfrac>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">)</m:mo>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mi>×</m:mi>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">(</m:mo>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mfrac>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>32</m:mn>
                    <m:mi>g</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    <m:mi mathvariant="italic">mol</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mfrac>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">)</m:mo>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mi>×</m:mi>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">(</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mfrac>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                      <m:mi mathvariant="italic">kg</m:mi>
                    </m:mrow>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mn>1000</m:mn>
                      <m:mi>g</m:mi>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mfrac>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">)</m:mo>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>79</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mi>g</m:mi>
            <m:msub>
              <m:mi>O</m:mi>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
            </m:msub>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">30 L  {C} rsub {8} {H} rsub {18}  × left ({0.75 kg} over {1 L} right ) × left ({1000 g} over {1 kg} right ) × left ({1 mol} over {114.22 g} right ) × left ({25 mol  {O} rsub {2}} over {2 mol  {C} rsub {8} {H} rsub {18}} right ) × left ({32 g} over {1 mol} right ) × left ({1 kg} over {1000 g} right ) =79 g  {O} rsub {2}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation>

</solution>
</exercise>

<exercise id="eip-388"><problem id="eip-494">
  <para id="eip-258">Suppose we desire a barrel that has a certain percentage hydrocarbons. If we need to obtain 200 gallons of crude oil that’s 80% hydrocarbons but the only available sources are barrel A (crude oil that’s 65% hydrocarbons) and barrel B (crude oil that’s 90% hydrocarbons), how much oil from each barrel should be used to produce the desired mixture?</para>
</problem>

<solution id="eip-772">
  <para id="eip-363">If we let <emphasis effect="italics">a</emphasis> be the number of gallons of barrel A and <emphasis effect="italics">b</emphasis> be the number of gallons of barrel B, we have a system of equations we can solve:</para>



<equation id="eip-992"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mi>a</m:mi>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
              <m:mi>b</m:mi>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
            <m:mn>200</m:mn>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">a+b=200</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation><equation id="eip-802"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>0.65</m:mn>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mi>a</m:mi>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
              <m:mn>0.90</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mi>b</m:mi>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>0.80</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">(</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>200</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">)</m:mo>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>160</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">0.65a+0.90b=0.80 left (200 right ) =160</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation><para id="eip-463">Using the <link target-id="eip-992"/> to get b = 200 – a and therefore:</para><equation id="eip-966"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>0.65</m:mn>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mi>a</m:mi>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
              <m:mn>0.90</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">(</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>200</m:mn>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>a</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">)</m:mo>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>180</m:mn>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                <m:mn>0.25</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mi>a</m:mi>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>160</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">0.65a+0.90 left (200-a right ) =180-0.25a=160</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation><equation id="eip-389"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mi>a</m:mi>
            <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mn>80</m:mn>
              <m:mo stretchy="false"> and </m:mo>
              <m:mi>b</m:mi>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
            <m:mn>120</m:mn>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">a=80  and b=120</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation>


</solution>
</exercise>




<exercise id="eip-397"><problem id="eip-758">
  <para id="eip-312">If barrel A contained 0.33% sulfur content while barrel B contained 0.62% sulfur content, would the mixture made in <link target-id="eip-388"/> be classified as sweet crude, sour crude, or neither?</para>
</problem>

<solution id="eip-125">

    

<para id="import-auto-idm235327136">We use our results from <link target-id="eip-388"/> to calculate the amount of sulfur content. First, we calculate that the fraction of mixture from barrels A and B are <link target-id="eip-691s"/> and <link target-id="eip-140"/>, respectively. </para><equation id="eip-691s"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mfrac>
              <m:mn>80</m:mn>
              <m:mn>200</m:mn>
            </m:mfrac>
            <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
            <m:mn>0.4</m:mn>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">{80} over {200} =0.4</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation><equation id="eip-140"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mfrac>
              <m:mn>120</m:mn>
              <m:mn>200</m:mn>
            </m:mfrac>
            <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
            <m:mn>0.6</m:mn>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">{120} over {200} =0.6</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation><para id="import-auto-idm508464752">Thus we have a total sulfur content of: </para>
    <equation id="eip-840"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mn>0.4</m:mn>
                      <m:mi>×</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>0.330</m:mn>
                      <m:mtext/>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mn>0.6</m:mn>
                      <m:mi>×</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>0.620</m:mn>
                      <m:mtext/>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="true">)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>0.504</m:mn>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mtext/>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">left (0.4 × 0.330% right ) + left (0.6 × 0.620% right ) =0.504%</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math></equation><para id="import-auto-idm215052544">Since this percentage is just above 0.5%, the mixture would be classified as sour crude.</para>
</solution>
</exercise><exercise id="eip-179"><problem id="eip-84">
  <para id="eip-455">A jet fuel analyst wants to correlate jet propulsion to the quantity of n-decane (C<sub>10</sub>H<sub>22</sub>) is found in their kerosene. After determining the thrust produced by a particular sample, she conducts UV-visible spectroscopy to determine the concentration within the sample. From this experiment, she finds the n-decane to have an absorbance of 0.698. The path length of her cuvette is 2.5 cm. From earlier experiments, she determines her molar absorptivity to be 12000 dm<sup>3</sup>mol<sup>-1</sup>cm<sup>-1</sup>. What is the concentration of n-decane in the sample?</para></problem>

<solution id="eip-817">
  <para id="eip-926">For this problem, we use Beer’s Law (<link target-id="eip-94"/>) to calculate the concentration (<link target-id="eip-638"/>).</para><equation id="eip-94"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mi>A</m:mi>
            <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
            <m:mi mathvariant="italic">εbc</m:mi>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">A=εbc</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </equation><equation id="eip-638"><m:math display="block">
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mi>c</m:mi>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mfrac>
                <m:mi>A</m:mi>
                <m:mi mathvariant="italic">εb</m:mi>
              </m:mfrac>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mfrac>
                <m:mn>0.698</m:mn>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mn>12000</m:mn>
                      <m:mi>d</m:mi>
                      <m:msup>
                        <m:mi>m</m:mi>
                        <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                      </m:msup>
                      <m:mi mathvariant="italic">mo</m:mi>
                      <m:msup>
                        <m:mi>l</m:mi>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                          <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:msup>
                      <m:mi>c</m:mi>
                      <m:msup>
                        <m:mi>m</m:mi>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                          <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:msup>
                      <m:mi>×</m:mi>
                      <m:mn>2.5</m:mn>
                      <m:mi mathvariant="italic">cm</m:mi>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo fence="true" stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mfrac>
              <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>2.3</m:mn>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo>
                <m:msup>
                  <m:mn>10</m:mn>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                    <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:msup>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:mi>M</m:mi>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">c= {A} over {εb} = {0.698} over {(12000   d {m} ^ {3} mo {l} ^ {-1} c {m} ^ {-1}  ×  2.5cm)} =2.3 x {10} ^ {-5} M</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math></equation>
</solution>
</exercise>
        
      </section><section id="import-auto-idm342704384">
        <title>Thought-provoking questions</title>
